		<pb n="1"/>
			<p>My dear <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Not wishing to allow you again to accuse me<lb/> of neglecting to send you any thing of interest that takes place<lb/> in our small congregation&#44; I hasten to make you acquainted with the<lb/> fact that &#34;The annual Examination of the Sunday School took place on<lb/> <date>Sunday 23 March</date>&#44; it was attended by our <add>&#63;</add> president and all the<lb/> members of the congregation. There were near thirty children<lb/> present and all acquitted themselves well. The elder boys under<lb/> the immediate tuition of our able Hazan the <persName>Revd Mr DeSola</persName><lb/> translated portions of the mishna&#44; Bible prayers &#38;c &#38;c<lb/> and were made to <sic>analyse</sic> several difficult sentences<lb/> which they did with great facility&#44; affording evidence of <del>his</del><lb/> the great progress they have made since last year. The<lb/> younger ones &#40;boys &#38; girls&#41; under the tuition of the Lady<lb/> teachers were carefully examined in &#34;Scripture Questions&#34;<lb/> &#34;Pykes Chatechism&#34; &#34;The Creed&#34; &#34;Ten Commandments&#34; and also<lb/> replied with great readiness and evinced great<lb/> imprisonment&#44; thus showing how faithfully their teachers<lb/> perform this pleasing <add>&#63;</add> they have voluntarily assumed</p>
			<p>Before commencing the examinations&#44; the whole together<lb/> sang <hi rend="underline">In Relohenu</hi><add>&#63;</add> in very good voice and closed with<lb/> repeating <del>all together</del> the <hi rend="underline">She<add>&#63;</add></hi>. <sic>Prises</sic> are not<lb/> distributed that way owing to some mistake&#44; but since which<lb/> all the most deserving have received some little token<lb/> as a reward for their exertions.&#34;</p>
			<p>I have nothing else of interest to offer you just now except</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>that part of the ceiling of the synagogue gave way some time<lb/> ago &#38; we have taken the opportunity which obliged to repair<lb/> to have the whole building cleaned &#38; the walls painted<lb/> which has much improved the appearance of our pretty<lb/> little place of worship. I have to thank you for the<lb/> proof you sent me of the presentation to <persName>Desola</persName> and<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> to congratulate you on the receipt of a similar present</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">In further news Refer you to our friend <persName>Graff<add>&#63;</add></persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(7)">I <add>&#63;</add> truly yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author"><add>&#63;</add></persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(7)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>20 March &#39;51</date></p>
          
